    <h4>Fasting and Abstinence</h4>

    <p>
      Fasting is a central pillar of the Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church’s spiritual life.
      Across the year, the faithful observe numerous fasts that cultivate discipline, humility,
      repentance, and deeper communion with God. There are approximately
      <strong>250 fast days</strong> annually, with about <strong>180</strong> being obligatory
      for believers above the age of 13.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Fasting Rules -->
  <div class="festivals-box">
    <h5 class="festivals-title">General Fasting Rules</h5>

    <ul class="festivals-list">
      <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> One meal a day, taken in the evening or after 2:45 p.m.</li>
      <li><strong>Diet:</strong> Abstention from meat, fats, eggs, and dairy; meals consist of cereals and vegetables.</li>
      <li><strong>Exemptions:</strong> No fasting during Christmas, Epiphany, and the 50 days between Easter and Pentecost.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Major Obligatory Fasts -->
  <div class="festivals-box">
    <h5 class="festivals-title">Major Obligatory Fasts</h5>

    <ul class="festivals-list">
      <li><strong>Great Lent (ዐብይ ነነዊ / ጾመ፡):</strong> 56 days.</li>
      <li><strong>Fast of the Apostles (ጾመ ነቢያት):</strong> 10–40 days (begins after Pentecost).</li>
      <li><strong>Fast of the Prophets / Advent Fast (ጾመ ነቢያት):</strong> 40 days before Christmas.</li>
      <li><strong>Fast of the Assumption of the Virgin Mary (ጾመ ፍልሰተ):</strong> 16 days.</li>
      <li><strong>Fast of Nineveh (ጾመ ነነዊ):</strong> 3 days (pre‑Lent).</li>
      <li><strong>Gahad (ገሐድ ጾም):</strong> Eves of Christmas and Epiphany.</li>
      <li><strong>Fast of Wellness / Fast of Salvation (ጾመ ዕንቁ፡):</strong> Every Wednesday & Friday (except during the 50 days after Easter).</li>
    </ul>
